<pre><code>Generator&lt;Integer&gt; simpleGenerator = new Generator&lt;Integer&gt;() {
    public void run() throws InterruptedException {
        yield(1);
        // Some logic here...
        yield(2);
    }
};
for (Integer element : simpleGenerator)
    System.out.println(element);
// Prints 1, then 2.
</code></pre>
<p>Infinite generators are also possible:</p>
<pre><code>Generator&lt;Integer&gt; infiniteGenerator = new Generator&lt;Integer&gt;() {
    public void run() throws InterruptedException {
        while (true)
            yield(1);
    }
};
